"# Appendix C — Instrument & Synth Vocabulary

Words used across the book, gathered here so a reader can point at a
term and jump back to the chapter where it lives. Nothing new is
introduced. If a word does not have a page here, it either did not
appear in the book or it appeared as a common word (like 'sound').

---

## Wave shapes

- **sine** — the simplest wave. Chapter 1.
- **square** — on/off wave, hollow and buzzy. Chapter 1.
- **saw** — ramp wave, bright and rich. Chapter 1.
- **triangle** — softer than square, mellower than saw. Chapter 1.
- **noise** — hash, no pitch. Chapter 6.

## Frequency & pitch

- **Hz** — cycles per second.
- **octave** — doubling of frequency.
- **fundamental** — the lowest partial you hear. Chapter 2.
- **harmonic / partial** — an integer multiple of the fundamental. Chapter 2.
- **overtone** — a partial above the fundamental. Chapter 2.

## Amplitude & envelope

- **attack / decay / sustain / release (ADSR)** — Chapter 5.
- **gain** — how loud.
- **clipping** — when a wave hits the ceiling. Chapter 3.

## Filters

- **low-pass / high-pass / band-pass** — Chapter 4.
- **cutoff** — the corner of a filter. Chapter 4.
- **resonance / Q** — the ring near the cutoff. Chapter 4.
- **formant** — a resonance that shapes vowels. Chapter 4, Chapter 15.

## Timing

- **BPM** — beats per minute. Chapter 11.
- **bar / measure** — a group of beats.
- **subdivision** — how a beat is split (16ths, triplets). Chapter 11.
- **swing** — the human late/early pattern. Chapter 12.

## Instrument parts

- **oscillator** — the source. Chapter 1.
- **soundboard** — the resonant body in physical models. Chapter 3, 7.
- **envelope generator** — the shape-of-loudness. Chapter 5.
- **filter section** — the color. Chapter 4.
- **effect (reverb, delay, chorus)** — the room around the sound.

## Sequencing

- **step sequencer** — Chapter 12.
- **arpeggiator** — Chapter 12.
- **chiptune** — old console sound. Chapter 12.
- **beat machine** — Chapter 16.

## Analysis words

- **FFT / spectrogram** — Chapter 13.
- **transcription** — from sound back to notes. Chapter 14.

## Voice

- **voiced / unvoiced** — with pitch, without. Chapter 15.
- **phoneme** — a speech unit. Chapter 15.

---

Point-and-return. That is what this appendix is for.")
